  "prompt": "How can I recover deleted photos from app lock new version?",
  "response": "Recovering deleted photos from any application can be challenging, particularly if the app does not offer a built-in recovery option. Here are some steps and strategies that might help you:\n\n1. **Check Trash/Recycle Bin:**\n   - Some app locks and gallery apps have a 'Trash' or 'Recycle Bin' feature where deleted photos are stored for a certain period before being permanently deleted. Check if your app lock has such a feature.\n\n2. **App Backup:**\n   - If you have configured the app to backup data to cloud services like Google Drive, Dropbox, or others, check these services to see if your photos are stored there.\n\n3. **Restore from Cloud Services:**\n   - If your photos were synced with cloud services such as Google Photos, iCloud, or others, you can restore them from there.\n\n4. **Device Backup:**\n   - If your device has been backing up data, like with Google Backup for Android or iCloud for iPhone, restore from the backup.\n\n5. **Third-party Recovery Tools:**\n   - There are several third-party recovery tools available for both Android and iOS, like DiskDigger, Dr.Fone, EaseUS MobiSaver, etc. Depending on your device, you can install a recovery tool and follow the instructions to scan for deleted photos.\n\n6. **Consult App Support:**\n   - Contact the app's customer support to check if they have any recommendations or built-in recovery options specific to the new version.\n\n7. **Manual Retrieval:**\n   - Explore your device\u2019s file manager for hidden folders where apps might store temporary data or versions of photos. Sometimes, app lock apps store files in hidden directories.\n\n**For Android:**\n1. **Connect to PC:**\n   - Connect your phone to a PC and use recovery software designed for Android devices.\n\n2. **Enable Developer Options:**\n   - Enable developer options and USB debugging on your Android device to allow certain recovery tools to access the phone\u2019s internal storage.\n\n**For iPhone:**\n1. **iTunes/Finder Backup:**\n   - If you've backed up your iPhone via iTunes or Finder, you can restore the backup to recover deleted photos.\n\n2. **Use Recovery Software:**\n   - Use iPhone-specific recovery software to scan for and recover deleted photos.\n\nAlways remember that the sooner you attempt to recover deleted photos, the better the chances of successful recovery. If too much time passes, new data can overwrite the old, making recovery impossible.",
